WEBVTT


00:00:11.741 --> 00:00:13.034
Should I open it?

00:00:13.118 --> 00:00:15.829
No. I'll do it if you're scared.

00:00:17.497 --> 00:00:19.207
I'm not scared.

00:00:36.349 --> 00:00:37.892
-I passed.
-Huh?

00:00:38.726 --> 00:00:40.061
I passed!

00:00:42.397 --> 00:00:44.315
Sorry!

00:00:44.399 --> 00:00:47.277
-Congrats, Johan!
-Look at Kanau. Congrats!

00:00:47.360 --> 00:00:48.194
It's a miracle!

00:00:48.278 --> 00:00:49.821
Sorry, Kanau.

00:00:49.904 --> 00:00:53.658
Man, I was worried because you said
your working holiday visa might expire.

00:00:53.741 --> 00:00:56.911
Wait, so if you pass
your college entrance exams…

00:00:56.995 --> 00:00:58.913
You can stay in Japan forever.

00:00:58.997 --> 00:01:00.999
I still have a long way to go.

00:01:02.458 --> 00:01:03.918
-We were loud, huh?
-Sorry.

00:01:04.002 --> 00:01:06.713
-Let's get you some milk.
-Yes, milk.

00:01:08.006 --> 00:01:09.174
There, there.

00:01:09.257 --> 00:01:10.091
Kanau.

00:01:10.175 --> 00:01:13.511
Come on. Time for some celebratory milk.

00:01:15.138 --> 00:01:19.309
Let's go to Mommy.
All right, we'll go to Mommy.

00:01:19.392 --> 00:01:21.603
See, she stopped crying.

00:01:23.771 --> 00:01:27.358
We usually only hire university graduates.

00:01:29.944 --> 00:01:32.739
I made an exception for you
because you're handsome.

00:01:34.073 --> 00:01:38.286
Make sure you get into university
and become a popular teacher, okay?

00:01:38.369 --> 00:01:39.204
Here.

00:01:41.206 --> 00:01:42.957
I'll do my very best.

00:01:45.585 --> 00:01:48.671
INSTRUCTOR
HWANG JOHAN

00:01:53.009 --> 00:01:54.677
Don't drink too much.

00:01:56.804 --> 00:01:58.765
I'm not drinking too much.

00:02:00.642 --> 00:02:02.227
You really worked hard.

00:02:03.394 --> 00:02:05.897
Sua was shocked too.

00:02:06.856 --> 00:02:10.526
She said she had no idea
her brother was this good at studying.

00:02:12.445 --> 00:02:14.072
Me too, to be honest.

00:02:22.538 --> 00:02:23.957
Well, I worked hard.

00:02:25.291 --> 00:02:28.127
Yeah. I really think you did.

00:02:40.098 --> 00:02:42.058
I guess I'll go easy on the drinks.

00:02:42.558 --> 00:02:44.060
Kanau's waiting for me.

00:02:44.143 --> 00:02:45.561
She's waiting for me.

00:02:47.397 --> 00:02:48.564
No, me.

00:02:49.899 --> 00:02:51.442
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

00:02:51.526 --> 00:02:52.944
Check, please.

00:02:53.736 --> 00:02:57.949
DAYCARECENTERS.COM

00:03:01.619 --> 00:03:02.954
Ryu.

00:03:03.037 --> 00:03:04.038
Hm?

00:03:06.708 --> 00:03:07.792
One of these days,

00:03:09.460 --> 00:03:12.213
I'm thinking of going to see
daycares for Kanau.

00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:13.881
Huh?

00:03:14.882 --> 00:03:17.760
But Kanau's only three months old.

00:03:18.261 --> 00:03:19.429
I know.

00:03:19.512 --> 00:03:24.934
But it's actually easier
to get into daycare at age zero.

00:03:26.019 --> 00:03:30.023
Well, I've kind of looked into it too.

00:03:33.651 --> 00:03:38.239
I've been thinking about
going back to work too.

00:03:40.325 --> 00:03:42.827
Like you and Johan.

00:03:43.828 --> 00:03:45.371
Everyone's working hard.

00:03:46.622 --> 00:03:48.207
So are you.

00:03:56.591 --> 00:03:58.384
I love Kanau.

00:04:00.553 --> 00:04:02.013
From the bottom of my heart.

00:04:04.724 --> 00:04:05.725
But…

00:04:06.642 --> 00:04:09.145
I want to work hard at my job too.

00:04:14.108 --> 00:04:15.693
Am I being selfish?

00:04:15.777 --> 00:04:17.278
No.

00:04:18.363 --> 00:04:19.781
Of course not.

00:04:21.115 --> 00:04:27.538
Let's not hold back when it comes to
Kanau, work, and our future.

00:04:28.122 --> 00:04:31.709
We'll work hard and go for it all.

00:04:35.880 --> 00:04:37.090
Thank you.

00:04:39.258 --> 00:04:42.053
-"Company employee" is fine, right?
-Yeah.

00:04:43.679 --> 00:04:47.767
RYU NARUTAKI, ROOMMATE
HWANG JOHAN, ROOMMATE

00:04:47.850 --> 00:04:49.477
Do you think she'll get in?

00:04:50.436 --> 00:04:51.562
Let's hope for it.

00:04:58.444 --> 00:04:59.862
Hello.

00:04:59.946 --> 00:05:01.197
-Hello.
-Hello.

00:05:01.280 --> 00:05:02.532
This way.

00:05:05.243 --> 00:05:08.371
-Thank you for coming.
-Yes, thank you.

00:05:08.454 --> 00:05:09.914
Thank you!

00:05:09.997 --> 00:05:11.958
-Bye-bye!
-Bye-bye!

00:05:18.172 --> 00:05:21.134
Ms. Aizawa, thank you for waiting.
Please come in.

00:05:28.683 --> 00:05:31.269
The performance will be
a fun event for all the children.

00:05:31.352 --> 00:05:34.272
We warmly welcome parents
to take part too.

00:05:35.481 --> 00:05:38.985
May I ask you one final question?

00:05:39.068 --> 00:05:40.069
Yes.

00:05:41.154 --> 00:05:45.908
I understand that
all of you are roommates.

00:05:45.992 --> 00:05:49.829
Um, what exactly is
your relationship to each other?

00:05:50.413 --> 00:05:53.708
I'd like to check
because this becomes relevant

00:05:53.791 --> 00:05:57.503
for authorized pickup,
as I mentioned earlier.

00:05:58.004 --> 00:06:00.631
Well, you see,

00:06:00.715 --> 00:06:05.094
these two are helping me raise her.

00:06:05.887 --> 00:06:07.305
Our "relationship"?

00:06:07.388 --> 00:06:08.806
Um…

00:06:08.890 --> 00:06:11.142
-May I say something?
-Yes.

00:06:12.727 --> 00:06:14.187
We…

00:06:15.897 --> 00:06:19.942
We'd like to become
Kanau's guardians if possible.

00:06:21.110 --> 00:06:24.530
We wrote "roommates"
on the application form,

00:06:25.031 --> 00:06:27.366
but we're not just living together.

00:06:28.326 --> 00:06:30.912
We may not be her parents,

00:06:31.662 --> 00:06:33.623
but we're serious.

00:06:34.874 --> 00:06:35.958
He's right.

00:06:36.042 --> 00:06:38.794
We are taking this seriously.

00:06:40.671 --> 00:06:43.549
Well, it might seem unusual,

00:06:43.633 --> 00:06:47.929
and I understand that
three guardians might sound strange.

00:06:48.429 --> 00:06:51.557
I don't think it's strange at all.

00:06:52.225 --> 00:06:57.355
I'd say we consider it
a unique family environment,

00:06:57.438 --> 00:07:00.566
but just because it's unique
doesn't mean it's bad.

00:07:01.734 --> 00:07:02.735
Right?

00:07:03.319 --> 00:07:04.320
Yes.

00:07:12.745 --> 00:07:14.455
This is a nice daycare center.

00:07:14.956 --> 00:07:15.957
Hm?

00:07:17.875 --> 00:07:19.877
I'm saying it's a nice place.

00:07:20.586 --> 00:07:23.714
Sumiko is back from maternity leave.

00:07:23.798 --> 00:07:24.757
Yes!

00:07:26.259 --> 00:07:27.093
Thank you.

00:07:27.176 --> 00:07:29.929
-You’re still gorgeous, even as a mom.
-Knock it off!

00:07:30.012 --> 00:07:32.348
-How have you been, Ms. Aizawa?
-I'm doing great.

00:07:32.431 --> 00:07:33.933
Welcome back, Sumi.

00:07:34.016 --> 00:07:35.017
Thanks.

00:07:35.101 --> 00:07:38.187
Sorry to jump right in,
but can I get your advice?

00:07:38.271 --> 00:07:40.189
Straight to business, huh? Sure.

00:07:40.273 --> 00:07:43.484
It's about the buttons
on the chest of this dress.

00:07:43.568 --> 00:07:44.569
Okay.

00:07:54.537 --> 00:07:56.414
All right. Let's go drinking.

00:07:56.497 --> 00:07:57.832
Good work today.

00:07:58.916 --> 00:08:02.211
You made sure to book a place
that has soju, right?

00:08:02.295 --> 00:08:04.630
I made sure to check.

00:08:04.714 --> 00:08:05.881
Good work.

00:08:05.965 --> 00:08:08.467
Phew, I'm tired.

00:08:08.551 --> 00:08:09.844
Good work today.

00:08:09.927 --> 00:08:11.053
You too, Mr. Johan.

00:08:12.305 --> 00:08:14.390
Johan, you too. Hurry up and let's go.

00:08:15.224 --> 00:08:17.184
No, I'll pass today.

00:08:17.268 --> 00:08:20.271
Come on, you're no fun.
You didn't come last time either.

00:08:22.106 --> 00:08:23.733
I have to go pick up my kid.

00:08:23.816 --> 00:08:26.193
What? You have a kid, Mr. Johan?

00:08:27.486 --> 00:08:29.113
Yes, I do.

00:08:31.282 --> 00:08:33.743
Then take your kid home and join us later.

00:08:33.826 --> 00:08:35.328
Leave your kid to your wife.

00:08:35.411 --> 00:08:39.457
I don't have money to go drinking.
If I did, I'd save it for my kid.

00:08:42.960 --> 00:08:45.463
-What's keeping you? Hurry up.
-Okay.

00:08:53.763 --> 00:08:54.972
Mr. Johan.

00:08:55.931 --> 00:08:59.685
If you're ever in need of money,
let me know.

00:09:00.269 --> 00:09:01.103
What?

00:09:01.187 --> 00:09:06.776
We're comrades.
We help each other in times of need.

00:09:13.949 --> 00:09:15.660
Hello.

00:09:15.743 --> 00:09:18.329
Oh, your pickup is here.

00:09:18.412 --> 00:09:20.748
There we go. Okay.

00:09:21.999 --> 00:09:23.834
Hello.

00:09:26.087 --> 00:09:29.590
-Kanau!
-She was in a good mood all day.

00:09:29.674 --> 00:09:31.133
Kanau.

00:09:32.426 --> 00:09:33.761
Hello.

00:09:34.637 --> 00:09:37.139
-All right, here you go.
-Thank you.

00:09:37.223 --> 00:09:39.517
Goodbye, Kanau.

00:09:39.600 --> 00:09:44.647
Kanau.

00:09:44.730 --> 00:09:46.273
You're not cold?

00:09:50.611 --> 00:09:52.363
Kanau, we're almost home.

00:09:53.030 --> 00:09:56.283
We're almost home, Kanau.

00:10:05.751 --> 00:10:08.212
-Hey, close the door.
-Okay.

00:10:11.090 --> 00:10:12.425
How's your fever?

00:10:12.508 --> 00:10:15.177
-It's gone down.
-Good.

00:10:15.261 --> 00:10:16.137
Yeah.

00:10:16.220 --> 00:10:18.764
All right. Here.

00:10:19.807 --> 00:10:21.016
Let's see.

00:10:21.976 --> 00:10:24.311
It hasn't gone down at all.

00:10:25.396 --> 00:10:27.356
You better take work off today.

00:10:27.440 --> 00:10:29.066
Okay.

00:10:33.154 --> 00:10:34.447
Whoa.

00:10:35.448 --> 00:10:36.866
And go see a doctor.

00:10:37.366 --> 00:10:40.161
If you want,
I can ask to take the day off too.

00:10:40.244 --> 00:10:42.413
-I can come with you--
-You're overreacting.

00:10:43.080 --> 00:10:44.707
It's just a cold.

00:10:44.790 --> 00:10:46.459
You don't know that.

00:10:46.542 --> 00:10:49.795
Even young people
can catch all sorts of illnesses.

00:10:49.879 --> 00:10:51.672
Yeah, yeah, Doctor.

00:10:52.173 --> 00:10:54.341
Doctor, huh?

00:10:54.425 --> 00:10:55.259
Here.

00:10:58.763 --> 00:10:59.764
Ouch.

00:11:08.773 --> 00:11:09.899
What's this?

00:11:09.982 --> 00:11:11.066
Rice porridge.

00:11:13.110 --> 00:11:14.779
-Can you eat?
-Yeah.

00:11:16.238 --> 00:11:17.990
Careful, it's hot.

00:11:19.533 --> 00:11:20.534
Here.

00:11:24.205 --> 00:11:28.793
We got a bit carried away
since we moved in with Kanau and Sumiko.

00:11:31.086 --> 00:11:32.463
That's true.

00:11:52.858 --> 00:11:54.276
Not bad, I guess.

00:11:56.237 --> 00:11:58.280
-You know what?
-What?

00:11:58.906 --> 00:11:59.865
Sumiko made that.

00:12:13.921 --> 00:12:18.551
Mr. Hwang Johan.
Please enter Exam Room One.

00:12:24.974 --> 00:12:26.851
So…

00:12:27.476 --> 00:12:29.478
I think it's just a cold.

00:12:29.562 --> 00:12:30.771
Okay.

00:12:30.855 --> 00:12:32.690
I'll put you on some medicine.

00:12:33.274 --> 00:12:34.900
Thank you.

00:12:35.442 --> 00:12:37.736
Oh, hold on a minute.

00:12:38.404 --> 00:12:39.989
Well, um…

00:12:40.072 --> 00:12:43.701
There's something else
that caught my attention.

00:12:43.784 --> 00:12:47.705
You wrote on your questionnaire
about some numbness in your body.

00:12:47.788 --> 00:12:48.914
Yes.

00:12:48.998 --> 00:12:51.584
Would you like to get that tested,
just in case?

00:12:53.460 --> 00:12:54.837
-Okay.
-Yeah?

00:12:55.337 --> 00:12:57.464
Then we'll draw some blood

00:12:57.965 --> 00:13:01.218
and look into the numbness in your body.

00:13:10.060 --> 00:13:10.895
FUMIE SASAKI

00:13:10.978 --> 00:13:14.064
We've done everything we can.

00:13:14.690 --> 00:13:20.529
But we must also consider
the other residents' lifestyles.

00:13:21.864 --> 00:13:27.328
With ongoing issues and complaints
from other residents and their families,

00:13:27.411 --> 00:13:33.292
we have no choice
but to ask her to vacate the facility.

00:13:33.375 --> 00:13:36.128
But it'll be worse if we take her home.

00:13:36.211 --> 00:13:39.465
Even professional caregivers struggle,
and we're not even trained.

00:13:39.548 --> 00:13:46.221
We will provide support
in finding a facility for Ms. Sasaki.

00:13:46.305 --> 00:13:48.849
We're the ones paying you though.

00:13:50.434 --> 00:13:55.064
When you're caring for your own parent,
does it matter if you're a professional?

00:14:09.244 --> 00:14:10.454
There we go.

00:14:11.956 --> 00:14:13.290
What's wrong?

00:14:15.167 --> 00:14:16.293
-Is she awake?
-Yeah.

00:14:16.377 --> 00:14:17.503
Oh, she is.

00:14:19.922 --> 00:14:21.590
I'm home.

00:14:21.674 --> 00:14:23.592
She's laughing.

00:14:23.676 --> 00:14:25.719
Welcome home.

00:14:25.803 --> 00:14:27.805
You drank a lot of milk.

00:14:27.888 --> 00:14:28.806
Are you full?

00:14:28.889 --> 00:14:30.224
You're full, aren't you?

00:14:30.307 --> 00:14:31.892
You're so chatty.

00:14:34.228 --> 00:14:35.062
I'll wash this.

00:14:35.145 --> 00:14:36.689
Thanks.

00:14:38.649 --> 00:14:39.858
How's Johan?

00:14:40.359 --> 00:14:42.319
He's home.
The doctor said it's just a cold.

00:14:42.403 --> 00:14:43.904
Okay.

00:14:45.447 --> 00:14:47.866
Is he still holed up in his room?

00:14:47.950 --> 00:14:50.869
Yeah. He said better safe than sorry.

00:14:58.419 --> 00:14:59.795
I'm coming in.

00:15:06.343 --> 00:15:08.804
How long are you gonna
stay shut up in here?

00:15:09.722 --> 00:15:12.057
At least until tomorrow.

00:15:12.766 --> 00:15:14.476
It's just a cold, right?

00:15:14.560 --> 00:15:17.646
That was what I said, wasn't it?

00:15:19.231 --> 00:15:21.984
So, did you wash your hands?

00:15:23.027 --> 00:15:24.278
I did.

00:15:26.572 --> 00:15:27.823
Did you gargle?

00:15:29.116 --> 00:15:30.492
Not yet.

00:15:30.993 --> 00:15:33.787
I always tell you to gargle
after you wash your hands--

00:15:33.871 --> 00:15:37.708
Yes, okay. I'm very sorry.

00:15:37.791 --> 00:15:39.293
-Hey.
-What?

00:15:39.376 --> 00:15:40.794
Close the door.

00:15:42.379 --> 00:15:44.089
Hey, you!

00:15:49.178 --> 00:15:50.471
Don't mess with me.

00:16:02.566 --> 00:16:04.318
So, I was thinking…

00:16:04.401 --> 00:16:08.781
It would be nice if we could express
this kind of image in that space.

00:16:08.864 --> 00:16:11.283
-Yeah.
-I agree.

00:16:13.285 --> 00:16:14.745
For example…

00:16:15.996 --> 00:16:18.916
We could incorporate a color like this.

00:16:18.999 --> 00:16:21.168
This emphasizes the seasonal theme.

00:16:21.251 --> 00:16:23.420
-True.
-That's wonderful.

00:16:23.504 --> 00:16:26.632
So, should we go ahead
with this color for the walls?

00:16:26.715 --> 00:16:28.425
Yeah, for now.

00:16:28.509 --> 00:16:30.928
I think we can move forward with this.

00:16:31.011 --> 00:16:33.639
-Sorry, just a moment.
-Sure.

00:16:33.722 --> 00:16:34.556
Hello?

00:16:34.640 --> 00:16:37.768
Hello? Ms. Aizawa, sorry to bother you.

00:16:37.851 --> 00:16:40.479
Kanau has a fever.

00:16:40.562 --> 00:16:41.814
Oh.

00:16:41.897 --> 00:16:44.399
Could you please come pick her up?

00:16:44.483 --> 00:16:47.027
Oh, um…

00:16:47.111 --> 00:16:51.740
We ask that children be picked up
if their temperature goes over 37.5°C.

00:16:51.824 --> 00:16:54.827
Right. Um, I'll head over.

00:16:54.910 --> 00:16:57.621
My meeting should be over
in about an hour.

00:17:11.635 --> 00:17:14.429
-Hello?
-Hello? Ms. Aizawa?

00:17:14.513 --> 00:17:18.559
-Speaking.
-Um, Kanau has a fever again.

00:17:18.642 --> 00:17:21.145
Can you come pick her up?

00:17:22.354 --> 00:17:25.149
Yes. I'll be right there.

00:17:25.232 --> 00:17:26.900
-I have a suggestion.
-Yeah?

00:17:26.984 --> 00:17:30.904
What if we completely open up
this shoulder area?

00:17:32.698 --> 00:17:33.866
I see.

00:17:33.949 --> 00:17:36.285
You're right. That might work.

00:17:36.368 --> 00:17:39.121
-From around here.
-Yeah.

00:17:39.204 --> 00:17:41.081
-That's nice.
-Yeah.

00:17:41.165 --> 00:17:43.333
-It looks good.
-Yeah.

00:17:47.504 --> 00:17:49.923
Go ahead and take it.
It's the daycare, right?

00:17:55.137 --> 00:17:56.471
Hello?

00:17:56.555 --> 00:18:00.642
"I have plans with a friend in Tokyo."

00:18:00.726 --> 00:18:05.105
-"I have plans with a friend in Tokyo."
-Good.

00:18:05.189 --> 00:18:09.401
Now, please practice this with each other.

00:18:09.484 --> 00:18:10.903
-Okay.
-Okay.

00:18:12.279 --> 00:18:13.530
Hello?

00:18:14.031 --> 00:18:15.991
-Oh, sorry, Johan.
-Yeah.

00:18:16.074 --> 00:18:18.744
I got a call that Kanau has a fever again.

00:18:19.244 --> 00:18:21.538
Can you go pick her up?

00:18:21.622 --> 00:18:23.707
I really can't leave work today.

00:18:23.790 --> 00:18:26.168
Ah, okay.

00:18:26.251 --> 00:18:30.088
I'll try asking if I can leave
in about 30 minutes.

00:18:30.589 --> 00:18:33.383
Yeah. No, it's fine.

00:18:33.467 --> 00:18:35.135
It's tough for Ryu.

00:18:35.219 --> 00:18:40.390
Caregivers have stricter rules.
Unlike me, he can't check his phone.

00:18:40.474 --> 00:18:41.892
We're lifting you up.

00:18:41.975 --> 00:18:43.894
Here. We're lifting you up now.

00:18:45.646 --> 00:18:47.189
There we go.

00:18:50.025 --> 00:18:52.319
Can you see the ocean, Ms. Sasaki?

00:18:53.237 --> 00:18:55.948
Ms. Sasaki, I know
you used to like this place.

00:18:58.533 --> 00:19:00.494
Can you see the ocean?

00:19:02.037 --> 00:19:03.372
There we go.

00:19:05.916 --> 00:19:07.626
It's beautiful.

00:19:21.890 --> 00:19:24.184
You're quiet today, aren't you?

00:19:34.444 --> 00:19:36.863
Mister?

00:19:37.364 --> 00:19:38.365
Hm?

00:19:41.827 --> 00:19:45.122
The thing about life is…

00:19:47.457 --> 00:19:51.628
There’s nothing you can
really do about it.

00:19:54.298 --> 00:19:55.299
Huh?

00:20:03.348 --> 00:20:07.561
Such sad sounds.

00:20:15.569 --> 00:20:18.238
So many things…

00:20:20.282 --> 00:20:25.120
just pass you by.

00:20:28.373 --> 00:20:30.000
But you know?

00:20:32.377 --> 00:20:38.133
There are also things that never change.

00:20:45.140 --> 00:20:46.516
Um…

00:20:51.563 --> 00:20:54.733
Thank you…

00:20:56.818 --> 00:20:59.863
for bringing me here.

00:21:05.827 --> 00:21:07.037
Sure.

00:21:23.261 --> 00:21:24.846
I'm home.

00:21:24.930 --> 00:21:26.890
-Welcome home.
-Welcome home.

00:21:29.601 --> 00:21:33.063
Sorry I've been getting home late
every day recently.

00:21:33.939 --> 00:21:37.442
Ms. Sasaki, was it?
Did you find her next nursing home?

00:21:37.526 --> 00:21:42.322
Not yet. I've been looking around
with my coworker, but it's not easy.

00:21:44.157 --> 00:21:45.700
The bath is ready.

00:21:45.784 --> 00:21:46.785
Okay.

00:21:48.495 --> 00:21:50.914
I guess I'll go take a bath now.

00:22:19.484 --> 00:22:21.611
Sumiko. Wanna drink this?

00:22:22.571 --> 00:22:23.738
Thanks.

00:22:24.406 --> 00:22:25.866
-I'll leave it here.
-Okay.

00:22:32.581 --> 00:22:34.499
Thanks for picking her up today.

00:22:36.334 --> 00:22:38.336
Call me anytime.

00:22:38.420 --> 00:22:43.884
If you want, we could ask the principal
to always call me.

00:22:43.967 --> 00:22:45.051
Ask the principal?

00:22:45.135 --> 00:22:47.095
Yeah. Why not?

00:22:58.482 --> 00:23:00.400
Wow, that's amazing.

00:23:00.484 --> 00:23:02.652
Kanau. Come here.

00:23:03.653 --> 00:23:05.572
All right. There, there.

00:23:11.661 --> 00:23:16.374
Kanau, my dear Kanau.

00:23:16.458 --> 00:23:18.168
Peekaboo.

00:23:20.003 --> 00:23:22.756
Kanau.

00:23:26.218 --> 00:23:29.429
Sorry. Just hang with me a bit longer.

00:23:30.889 --> 00:23:32.390
Mr. Hwang.

00:23:32.474 --> 00:23:34.142
Mr. Hwang Johan.

00:23:34.226 --> 00:23:35.143
Yes?

00:23:35.227 --> 00:23:36.561
Please come this way.

00:23:41.274 --> 00:23:42.859
Let's go.

00:23:43.818 --> 00:23:46.238
I didn't know you had a child.

00:23:46.738 --> 00:23:47.822
I do.

00:23:47.906 --> 00:23:49.950
I'm Kanau!

00:23:51.326 --> 00:23:53.161
So, Mr. Hwang.

00:23:54.079 --> 00:23:56.706
Your blood test didn't show any issues.

00:23:56.790 --> 00:23:59.167
But, well…

00:24:00.126 --> 00:24:03.755
These are the results
from your electromyography test.

00:24:05.340 --> 00:24:06.800
ALS.

00:24:07.300 --> 00:24:10.470
Or it could be SBMA.

00:24:11.096 --> 00:24:13.723
They are hard to distinguish.

00:24:14.391 --> 00:24:17.602
But there is a possibility
it could be an intractable disease.

00:24:19.729 --> 00:24:22.732
Oh, um…

00:24:24.693 --> 00:24:29.573
What are ALS and SBMA?

00:24:29.656 --> 00:24:30.991
With either condition,

00:24:31.074 --> 00:24:35.161
the muscles in your entire body
will incrementally stop moving.

00:24:35.829 --> 00:24:40.000
And eventually,
you won't be able to breathe on your own.

00:24:40.500 --> 00:24:41.960
It is a progressive disease.

00:24:50.927 --> 00:24:52.804
It can be cured, right?

00:24:53.305 --> 00:24:54.973
At this stage,

00:24:55.724 --> 00:24:59.894
I'm sorry to say that
there is no cure for this disease.

00:25:01.688 --> 00:25:03.773
For diseases like this,

00:25:03.857 --> 00:25:09.571
we recommend that you get tested
and treated in your home country.

00:25:11.698 --> 00:25:14.409
Not only because of medical costs,

00:25:15.493 --> 00:25:19.372
but also because support from your family
will be extremely important.

00:25:21.708 --> 00:25:22.792
What do you think?

00:25:23.668 --> 00:25:26.463
Why don't you consider
getting treatment in Korea?

00:25:36.181 --> 00:25:37.766
Chubby?

00:25:38.391 --> 00:25:40.852
-Chubby.
-Chubby.

00:25:41.645 --> 00:25:43.188
Oh, sorry.

00:25:44.272 --> 00:25:46.274
-Ryu.
-Yeah?

00:25:46.358 --> 00:25:48.443
You have an early shift tomorrow, right?

00:25:48.526 --> 00:25:49.527
Yeah.

00:25:50.528 --> 00:25:53.323
Can you pick up Kanau?

00:25:53.406 --> 00:25:54.658
Of course.

00:25:56.034 --> 00:25:58.328
Uncle Ryu's gonna pick you up tomorrow.

00:25:58.411 --> 00:26:01.373
-Isn't that great?
-Woo-hoo!

00:26:01.915 --> 00:26:03.166
Sorry.

00:26:04.000 --> 00:26:08.213
I might be too busy
to pick her up for a while.

00:26:08.296 --> 00:26:09.714
Studying for your exams?

00:26:11.675 --> 00:26:12.676
Yeah.

00:26:13.510 --> 00:26:15.553
Good luck.

00:26:25.897 --> 00:26:29.317
It's rare for you to call me over.

00:26:31.444 --> 00:26:33.238
Wow.

00:26:33.321 --> 00:26:35.281
I didn't know about this place.

00:26:52.132 --> 00:26:53.591
You mentioned before

00:26:55.343 --> 00:26:57.178
about helping if I ever needed money.

00:26:57.262 --> 00:26:58.805
Oh, yes.

00:26:58.888 --> 00:27:00.515
What about it?

00:27:02.434 --> 00:27:04.227
What exactly did you mean?

00:27:06.855 --> 00:27:11.860
Okay, this round's on the house!

00:27:17.866 --> 00:27:18.825
-Ready?
-Ready?

00:27:18.908 --> 00:27:21.661
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

00:27:39.846 --> 00:27:42.932
Why don't you try calling him
if you're that worried?

00:27:43.683 --> 00:27:45.435
Well…

00:27:45.518 --> 00:27:47.645
He must be busy with this and that.

00:27:51.691 --> 00:27:53.735
You had a lot to drink, huh?

00:27:53.818 --> 00:27:55.987
Are you okay?

00:27:56.070 --> 00:28:00.825
Oh, no. You can't do that here.

00:28:02.827 --> 00:28:05.121
But it was fun, wasn't it?

00:28:05.205 --> 00:28:06.956
-Wait.
-Oh.

00:28:12.754 --> 00:28:13.880
Hello?

00:28:14.464 --> 00:28:15.924
-Hello!
-Hello?

00:28:16.424 --> 00:28:17.258
Huh?

00:28:17.342 --> 00:28:19.511
-Um…
-Are you from Mr. Johan's household?

00:28:19.594 --> 00:28:21.805
-Uh, yes. Who is this?
-Oh, sorry.

00:28:21.888 --> 00:28:25.683
Mr. Johan kinda got drunk
and passed out tonight.

00:28:25.767 --> 00:28:26.810
What?

00:28:26.893 --> 00:28:30.146
Oh, uh, I'll come pick him up then.

00:28:30.230 --> 00:28:31.147
It's okay.

00:28:31.231 --> 00:28:33.024
I live nearby, so he can stay over.

00:28:33.107 --> 00:28:35.610
Oh, no. I'd feel bad.

00:28:35.693 --> 00:28:37.821
Don't worry about it. Oh!

00:28:37.904 --> 00:28:40.532
I-I'll hang up now. Sorry!

00:28:40.615 --> 00:28:42.826
Huh? Wait.

00:28:42.909 --> 00:28:44.327
Mr. Johan!

00:29:06.266 --> 00:29:07.475
Sumiko?

00:29:11.855 --> 00:29:13.565
Kanau has a fever?

00:29:14.774 --> 00:29:17.277
Oh, right.

00:29:17.360 --> 00:29:21.865
But I'm working this afternoon.

00:29:22.782 --> 00:29:25.243
Yeah. What should we do?

00:29:26.619 --> 00:29:28.037
Yeah.

00:29:29.622 --> 00:29:30.915
Hold on a second.

00:29:31.791 --> 00:29:33.042
Mr. Johan.

00:29:33.835 --> 00:29:36.045
I'll take over your class for you.

00:29:36.546 --> 00:29:38.131
-Really?
-Yes.

00:29:38.214 --> 00:29:39.340
Thank you.

00:29:40.008 --> 00:29:43.720
Oh, Sumiko. I can go after all.

00:29:44.220 --> 00:29:46.180
Yeah. Got it.

00:29:48.850 --> 00:29:51.185
-Thank you so much.
-Sure.

00:29:51.895 --> 00:29:54.063
-Are you going already?
-Yes, I'll head out.

00:29:54.147 --> 00:29:56.816
Mr. Johan, your bag.

00:29:58.109 --> 00:29:59.736
-Take care.
-Thanks.

00:29:59.819 --> 00:30:01.821
-I'll be off. See you later.
-Okay.

00:30:06.534 --> 00:30:07.869
Hello.

00:30:14.042 --> 00:30:17.545
Oh, Mr. Johan.
Feels like it's been a while.

00:30:17.629 --> 00:30:19.130
Yes, it's been a while.

00:30:19.213 --> 00:30:20.798
How's Kanau?

00:30:20.882 --> 00:30:21.925
She's okay.

00:30:22.008 --> 00:30:24.093
It seems her fever's gone down too.

00:30:25.803 --> 00:30:27.972
-Yes?
-I'm opening the door.

00:30:30.600 --> 00:30:32.268
Her pickup's here.

00:30:33.394 --> 00:30:34.812
Kanau.

00:30:34.896 --> 00:30:36.689
She's doing much better.

00:30:37.190 --> 00:30:38.399
Kanau.

00:30:38.983 --> 00:30:40.985
Are you okay?

00:30:43.905 --> 00:30:44.948
Thank you.

00:30:57.627 --> 00:30:58.836
We're home.

00:30:58.920 --> 00:31:01.214
-We're home.
-Welcome home.

00:31:06.844 --> 00:31:09.305
-Thanks for today. You saved me.
-No problem.

00:31:09.389 --> 00:31:11.641
-Has her fever gone down?
-Yeah, it has.

00:31:11.724 --> 00:31:12.934
What a relief.

00:31:26.823 --> 00:31:27.657
Hey.

00:31:27.740 --> 00:31:29.534
Hey, welcome home.

00:31:39.335 --> 00:31:41.170
I'm going out for a bit.

00:31:41.254 --> 00:31:42.255
Huh?

00:31:55.268 --> 00:31:56.602
Where are you going?

00:32:01.691 --> 00:32:03.109
I made plans.

00:32:03.192 --> 00:32:04.986
Plans?

00:32:10.283 --> 00:32:12.994
You know, like yesterday too.

00:32:13.494 --> 00:32:14.912
At least answer your phone.

00:32:17.165 --> 00:32:17.999
Sorry.

00:32:18.082 --> 00:32:20.084
No. I don't want to hear "sorry."

00:32:20.168 --> 00:32:21.169
Sorry.

00:32:21.919 --> 00:32:23.629
I'll be sure to answer my phone.

00:32:24.630 --> 00:32:27.008
Okay, I'm heading out.

00:32:38.352 --> 00:32:43.066
Yes! I'm in a good mood.
This one's on the house today!

00:32:54.952 --> 00:32:55.912
What?

00:32:55.995 --> 00:32:58.915
You gotta watch out
for punch-drunk syndrome and stuff.

00:32:58.998 --> 00:32:59.999
Johan!

00:33:04.128 --> 00:33:06.297
You're getting out of shape, huh?

00:33:44.710 --> 00:33:45.711
Hm?

00:33:49.006 --> 00:33:50.591
You're still awake.

00:33:52.009 --> 00:33:53.803
Do you have any idea what time it is?

00:33:53.886 --> 00:33:55.680
Hmm.

00:34:03.688 --> 00:34:06.774
Oh. It's still only one o'clock.

00:34:08.693 --> 00:34:11.112
Sweetfish…

00:34:19.036 --> 00:34:22.123
Washing my hands.

00:34:22.206 --> 00:34:23.624
-Hey.
-Washing my--

00:34:23.708 --> 00:34:26.252
Kanau and Sumiko are sleeping.
Keep it down.

00:34:26.335 --> 00:34:27.503
Huh?

00:34:27.587 --> 00:34:29.463
They're sleeping.

00:34:29.964 --> 00:34:31.424
Oh.

00:34:38.431 --> 00:34:43.227
Kanau!

00:34:43.311 --> 00:34:44.770
Hey, stop that.

00:34:45.438 --> 00:34:47.690
-Stop.
-Huh?

00:34:47.773 --> 00:34:49.817
Let go of me!

00:34:51.611 --> 00:34:53.571
Over there. Go over there.

00:34:54.071 --> 00:34:56.616
Okay, okay.

00:35:04.582 --> 00:35:06.375
You're way too drunk.

00:35:06.876 --> 00:35:08.211
Damn.

00:35:09.128 --> 00:35:11.088
Shut up.

00:35:11.172 --> 00:35:13.090
You're the one that needs to shut up.

00:35:14.967 --> 00:35:17.386
-What?
-What do you mean "what"?

00:35:17.470 --> 00:35:21.432
What's with you?
You've been acting weird lately.

00:35:23.726 --> 00:35:26.145
I just went drinking for a bit.

00:35:26.229 --> 00:35:28.314
Right now, we need to support each other.

00:35:30.149 --> 00:35:32.318
Support each other?

00:35:33.236 --> 00:35:34.445
Meanwhile, you…

00:35:36.405 --> 00:35:38.032
You rarely pick Kanau up.

00:35:38.115 --> 00:35:39.825
That's why I do the housework.

00:35:39.909 --> 00:35:41.202
I do it too.

00:35:41.786 --> 00:35:43.120
So does Sumiko.

00:35:45.831 --> 00:35:49.377
You're the one
who's always coming home late.

00:35:49.460 --> 00:35:51.212
You don't answer your phone either.

00:35:51.712 --> 00:35:55.091
Sumiko and I are the ones
watching Kanau during that time.

00:35:55.174 --> 00:35:56.634
I can't use my phone at work.

00:35:56.717 --> 00:35:58.427
We all work!

00:36:00.680 --> 00:36:02.431
Keep it down.

00:36:13.693 --> 00:36:15.278
I came all the way to Japan.

00:36:18.406 --> 00:36:22.243
And you give me a hard time
for going out a few times.

00:36:28.332 --> 00:36:30.251
You asked me to come to Japan.

00:36:31.419 --> 00:36:32.503
What?

00:36:33.379 --> 00:36:35.798
Sumiko and Seiichi.

00:36:36.674 --> 00:36:40.136
They were your friends to begin with.

00:36:41.804 --> 00:36:43.889
Why would you say it like that?

00:36:45.891 --> 00:36:46.934
What?

00:36:47.435 --> 00:36:50.187
Are you saying
I dragged you here against your will?

00:36:51.605 --> 00:36:53.316
I never said that.

00:36:54.233 --> 00:36:59.488
You were in such a bad state,
so I suggested you live here--

00:36:59.572 --> 00:37:00.948
Don't look down on me!

00:37:02.283 --> 00:37:03.993
I said don't look down on me.

00:37:09.415 --> 00:37:10.333
Did you

00:37:12.168 --> 00:37:17.173
bring me here out of pity?

00:37:19.592 --> 00:37:22.219
This whole time…

00:37:24.680 --> 00:37:27.141
did you feel sorry for me?

00:37:29.727 --> 00:37:31.437
That wasn't what I meant.

00:37:35.649 --> 00:37:36.650
Then…

00:37:38.861 --> 00:37:40.571
what did you mean?

00:37:41.739 --> 00:37:43.115
It's…

00:38:10.351 --> 00:38:12.311
I found someone I care about.

00:38:16.649 --> 00:38:17.650
What?

00:38:20.778 --> 00:38:22.988
Someone I want to protect.

00:38:24.407 --> 00:38:25.574
Someone that means…

00:38:28.119 --> 00:38:29.995
more to me than anything else.

00:38:33.499 --> 00:38:34.959
I want to…

00:38:39.922 --> 00:38:41.549
make that person happy.

00:38:42.216 --> 00:38:43.467
No, wait.

00:38:46.679 --> 00:38:47.555
What?

00:38:47.638 --> 00:38:49.807
W-Wait a minute.

00:38:51.517 --> 00:38:53.060
What are you saying?

00:38:53.936 --> 00:38:55.396
No way.

00:38:55.896 --> 00:38:56.814
What?

00:38:57.857 --> 00:38:59.859
I can't believe you're doing this.

00:38:59.942 --> 00:39:00.943
I know.

00:39:02.862 --> 00:39:03.696
Sorry.

00:39:03.779 --> 00:39:05.239
I don't want "sorry."

00:39:05.322 --> 00:39:08.033
-Sorry.
-I said stop apologizing!

00:39:09.785 --> 00:39:10.786
I'll…

00:39:12.621 --> 00:39:13.539
move out.

00:39:19.295 --> 00:39:22.923
I enjoyed the time we spent together.

00:39:27.803 --> 00:39:30.806
But I can't stay with you anymore.

00:41:04.817 --> 00:41:05.818
Bye.

00:41:20.833 --> 00:41:23.752
Please throw away the rest of my stuff.

00:41:35.264 --> 00:41:36.682
About him…

00:41:37.558 --> 00:41:38.767
Take care of him, okay?

00:41:43.397 --> 00:41:44.815
Kanau.

00:41:50.070 --> 00:41:51.572
Take care.

00:41:58.495 --> 00:42:00.247
Thank you for everything.

00:46:17.838 --> 00:46:20.757
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura